reviews.review_text: hansokolow does it again boom your back in the stadium 1991

Creative Setlist, Mixed Performance This is a show that is bound to be overshadowed by the first night of the Shoreline 91' August run. That Scarlet>Victim>Fire is a jam for the ages. This show suffers from occasional false starting, missed cues on both Bobby and Jerry's part and hit or miss energy. 

However the second set is obviously interesting. Perhaps they were running out of "second set songs" since this tour they played an entirely different set song-for-song for six nights in a row. Either way the Deal that starts set 2 is slammin' especially due to Bruce's enthusiasm. Samson that follows is over-shadowed by Greensboro 91' Samson but still kills. Half-Step is sloppy but picks up some steam in the final solo. Stranger is mystical, slowed down, spacey and jive. The highlight of the evening next to the other jivey and sped up rendition of West L.A. which again is punched up by Bruce. Bob seems to be having fun at this show, at times a little too fun and he gets a little ahead of himself Bobby style. 

All in all some really solid effort at moments but not a five star show due there being many more i would choose to listen to from 91' before this one, however still worth a listen and notable for a cool setlist and moments of real solid jamming.
